          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>to a shallow bowl</p><p>Combine the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>shichimi togarashi</strong> on separate plate</p><p>Coat the <strong>flattened steaks</strong> in the flour, tap off any excess, then add to the <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and finally press into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to evenly coat all over – these are your <strong>breaded steaks</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
